@node Main "Windows V1.1"
                               @{" < Table of Contents " link "Macro-Package.guide/Main"}

@{fg shine}Benefits: @{fg text}
   Easy arrangment of multiple open windows.
   Especially useful for copying things from one window into another.

@{fg shine}Using the @{"macro" system "Sys:Utilities/Multiview Windows.iff"}:@{fg text}

   A@{fg fill}r@{fg text}range
      Please choose how all the open windows should be arranged.
         - Normal (one behind the other)
         - Tile vertically
         - Tile horizontally
         - Cascade
      @{fg shine}Note:@{fg text}
      The functions "Tile vertically" & "Tile horizontally" depend on the
      current screen resolution. £Final Writer¨ only allows to reduce window
      size down to a certain size.
         e.g.:  Resolution: 1280 * 512
                - Tile vertically   = 6 windows
                - Tile horizontally = 2 windows

                Resolution: 800 * 600
                - Tile vertically   = 4 windows
                - Tile horizontally = 3 windows  and so on

                     - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - 

   @{fg fill}A@{fg text}pply
      Start arranging the windows. 

   @{fg fill}C@{fg text}ancel
   @{fg fill}ESC@{fg text} or close window
      Quit the macro.

@endnode
